Given an array of integers nums, find the maximum length of a subarray where the product of all its elements is positive.

A subarray of an array is a consecutive sequence of zero or more values taken out of that array.

Return the maximum length of a subarray with positive product.

class Solution {
    public int getMaxLen(int[] nums) {
        int posLen = 0;
        int negLen = 0;
        int ans = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        for(int num:nums){
            //if current is 0, we reset lenth of positive and negative
            if(num == 0){
                posLen = 0;
                negLen = 0;
            }else if(num > 0){
                //if current is positive, length of positive should be increased by 1
                //if negative length is not 0, we increase it by 1
                posLen++;
                negLen = negLen==0? 0:negLen+1;
            }else{
                //if current is negative, we swap the length of positive and negative
                int temp = posLen;
                posLen = negLen==0? 0:negLen+1;
                negLen = temp+1;
            }
            ans = Math.max(ans, posLen);
            
        }
        
        return ans;
        
    }
}
